I've decided to move forward with a simulated Google login flow, prioritizing user experience and preventing the need for complex setup. The initial idea of using `localStorage` for the mock is dropped; the aim is a purely visual simulation mirroring the sign-in experience. My design now centers on creating a high-fidelity UI that emulates the process without relying on backend authentication. I now focus on rendering the UI for the Google login button.


