I'm now focused on the UI, specifically the styling and structure of the Google sign-in button and the "OR" divider. I need the Google button to look distinct from the primary sign-in button, aiming for a white background, a gray border, and text that is a darker gray. I've also constructed mock user data with a generic Google avatar. I'm prioritizing the visual feel of the Google button, and have decided it needs to have a premium appearance, matching the existing app aesthetics.

